{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Mehmet Nazif Günal | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age |1948}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Turkish | residence = [[Istanbul]], Turkey | education = | alma mater = [[Middle East Technical University]] | occupation = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = chairman and 100% owner of MNG Holding | boards = | salary = | networth = US$1.62 billion (April 2017)<ref name="forbes1" /> | spouse = married | children = 3 | parents = | relations = | website = }}
'''Mehmet Nazif Günal''' (born 1948) is a Turkish [[billionaire]] property developer, the chairman and 100% owner of MNG Holding,<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/mehmet-nazif-gunal/ |title=Mehmet Nazif Gunal |publisher=Forbes.com |accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> and [[MNG Airlines]].
Günal was born in 1948.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|author=Mng Group Of Companies |url=http://www.mng.com.tr/eng/corporate.php?sf=corporate_&k=43&u=130 |title=Mng Şirketler Topluluğu |publisher=Mng.com.tr |date= |accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> He has bachelor's and master's degree in civil engineering from [[Middle East Technical University]], Ankara.<ref name="autogenerated1"/><ref name="forbes1"/>
Günal owns ten 5-star hotels, the WoW (World of Wonders) Kremlin Palace and the WoW Topkapi Palace, in Antalya, are "architecturally exact replicas" of the [[Kremlin]] and [[Topkapı Palace|Topkapi]] palaces.<ref name="forbes1"/>
Günal is married, with three children, and lives in [[Istanbul]], Turkey.<ref name="forbes1"/>
